article.headline: Stephen F. Austin 101, Paul Quinn 48
article.story: NACOGDOCHES, Texas (AP) -- Josh Alexander and Matt Kingsley each had a double-double in Stephen F. Austin's 101-48 rout of winless Paul Quinn on Saturday night. Alexander, a starter, had 13 points and 10 rebounds, while Kingsley added 18 points and 10 rebounds off the bench. Stephen F. Austin (6-2) had three other players in double figures -- Antuane Miller with a game-high 19 points, Anthony Paez with 17 and Chaz Dykes with 10. Paul Quinn (0-10) shot just 29 percent from the field (16-of-56) and was out-rebounded 58-13. Demetrices Edwards led the team with 11 points off the bench. Stephen F. Austin shot 63 percent, led by Paez (8-of-9) and Kingsley (8-of-11).
